The policy is uniquely defined by an ID and has a name, type, coverage, term, premium and returns. An agent is assigned a branch and hold a list of policyholders they've insured. A public relation advisor is assigned to every policyholder throughout the policy term, irrespective of the number of policies they hold. A public relation advisor can handle multiple policyholders. A customer can renew, suspend or file claims over an existing policy, given the claim date is within the policy term. The policyholder pays the premium based on the payment term, which can be monthly, quarterly, bi-annual, annual or one-time.&nbsp;</div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;"><br style="forced-color-adjust: none;"></div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;"><b style="forced-color-adjust: none;">Relations</b></div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;">A customer holds one or more policies</div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;">An agent insures one or more customers</div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;">A PR advisor is assigned to every policyholder. But one PR can handle accounts of multiple customers.</div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;">A customer pays for a policy. This payment can be recurring which repeats after a certain interval.</div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;">A policy's permium is paid by a payment. There can be one or more payments associated to a policy</div><div style="forced-color-adjust: none;"><br></div>" div.div: A customer is unique and can hold multiple policies. The policy is uniquely defined by an ID and has a name, type, coverage, term, premium and returns. An agent is assigned a branch and hold a list of policyholders they've insured. A public relation advisor is assigned to every policyholder throughout the policy term, irrespective of the number of policies they hold. A public relation advisor can handle multiple policyholders. A customer can renew, suspend or file claims over an existing policy, given the claim date is within the policy term. The policyholder pays the premium based on the payment term, which can be monthly, quarterly, bi-annual, annual or one-time.Â
